    "breadcrumb": "Hands-on Amazon GameLift \u003e 2. Setup",
    "content": "What you’re deploying Two CDK stacks — the web half of the game, no GameLift yet:\nPixelRushBackendStack — API Gateway + Lambda + DynamoDB (login, garage, shop, leaderboard, matchmaking API) and a WebSocket API for notifications PixelRushFrontendStack — the Phaser web client on CloudFront + private S3 1. Deploy From the infra/ directory:\nnpx cdk deploy PixelRushBackendStack PixelRushFrontendStack --require-approval never Takes ~6 minutes. Note two outputs at the end:\nPixelRushBackendStack.ApiUrl = https://xxxx.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com PixelRushBackendStack.WsNotifyUrl = wss://yyyy.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/prod PixelRushFrontendStack.SiteUrl = https://zzzz.cloudfront.net Tip Save ApiUrl somewhere — you’ll paste it into the game in Module 6 to prove your deployment works end to end.\n2. Wire the frontend config Write the WebSocket URL into the frontend config, rebuild, and redeploy the site:\necho \"{ \\\"wsNotifyUrl\\\": \\\"\u003cPASTE-WsNotifyUrl-HERE\u003e\\\" }\" \u003e ../frontend/public/config.json (cd ../frontend \u0026\u0026 npm run build) npx cdk deploy PixelRushFrontendStack --require-approval never 3. Checkpoint ★ Open SiteUrl in your browser:\nEnter any racer name + the workshop password gamelift → START ENGINE You land in the lobby with a random starter persona (level, coins, a car) Browse GARAGE and SHOP — buy a car if you have the coins! Info Try clicking RACE → a track → 2P: matchmaking will spin forever. That’s expected — there is no game server anywhere yet. Fixing that is the rest of this workshop.",
