    "content": "Info AWS event path: skip this page — temporary accounts are wiped automatically after the event.\nOne command cd infra npx cdk destroy PixelRushGameLiftStack PixelRushFrontendStack PixelRushBackendStack --force Takes ~10 minutes (fleet termination dominates). You can close the terminal — deletion continues server-side.\nVerify (the bill-safe checklist) The only resource with a meaningful hourly cost is the fleet instance. Confirm:\nConsole → GameLift → Fleets: PixelRushFleet is Deleting or gone Console → CloudFormation: all three PixelRush* stacks show DELETE_COMPLETE (or are absent) Optional: GameLift → Builds — builds are retained by default and cost nothing to keep, but you can delete PixelRushServer manually Tip Everything else (Lambda, DynamoDB on-demand, API Gateway, CloudFront) is pay-per-request — zero traffic means zero cost even if deletion lags.",
